Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
A unique working farm situated in beautiful natural surrounds.

Picturesque mountain backdrop, views across the Yarra Valley, a large clear water dam stocked with native fish, plus the fast flowing Yarra River on the boundary are only a few of the many outstanding features of this magnificent property.

Registered dam and pumping licence from the Yarra River ensure a plentiful supply of clean water for any farming enterprise.

A magnificent amphitheatre setting, providing a micro-climate with frost free conditions on slightly undulating land with an open aspect. Highly fertile and well drained mountain and sandy loam soils. Situated at the top end of the Yarra Valley at Millgrove. Potential for farm sales, small caf√© and value added products.

A well-documented history of professional management procedures and acknowledged bio security measures preserve the disease free status of this property. Implementing environmentally conscious farming practices, the site is recognised widely by government and industry institutions as a benchmark for modern farming standards. Awarded the 2019 Australian Farm Biosecurity Producer of the year.

Extensive and modern improvements. Main high clearance insulated building of 1000sq m approx. Includes climate controlled processing and packing area, 2 x 24 pallet coolrooms, office, staff kitchen and tea room, loading and dispatch area, workshop and a 125KVA backup generator to facilitate main building. External buildings, total 492sq m includes pumping station, machinery shed and storage building.

3 x variable stage computer controlled pumps, (CR65 Grundfos),high pressure underground mains with 36 x 3-4 inch solonoids with automatic filtration throughout the entire farm, allowing for precise and monitored watering and fertigation. 8ha under shade cloth.

A comprehensive list of extremely well maintained plant and equipment for purchase separately or by negotiation.

Inspection strictly by appointment and accompanied by the agent.
In conjunction with Val Nicholls 0428 534 434
